"Find each unknown number: 22. (3) a + 60 + 70 = 180 23. (85) 4 w 24. (79) The perimeter of this square is 48 in. What is the area of one of the triangles? Refer to the table below to answer problems 25–27. Mark’s Personal Running Records Distance Time (minutes:seconds) 4 mile 0:58 2 mile 2:12 1 mile 5:00 25. (32) If Mark set his 1-mile record by keeping a steady pace, then what was his 1 2-mile time during the 1-mile run? 26. (32) Conclude What is a reasonable expectation for the time it would take Mark to run 2 miles? A 9:30 B 11:00 C 15:00 27. (32) Formulate Write a question that relates to this table and answer the question. * 28. (97) Transversal t intersects parallel lines r and s. Angle 2 measures 78°. r s t a. Analyze Which angle corresponds to ∠2? b. Find the measures of ∠5 and ∠8. * 29. (92) 102 249 (10 8) 32 30. (58) What is the probability of rolling a composite number with one roll of a number cube?"
"Sum of the Angle Measures of Triangles and Quadrilaterals Power Up Building Power facts Power Up J mental math a. Number Sense: 40 ∙ 50 b. Number Sense: 293 + 450 c. Percent: 50% of 48 d. Calculation: $20.00 − $18.72 e. Decimals: 12.5 × 100 f. Number Sense: 360 g. Measurement: How many cups are in 2 pints? h. Calculation: 8 × 8, − 1, ÷ 9, × 4, + 2, ÷ 2, + 1, 2 , 2 problem solving If two people shake hands, there is one handshake. If three people shake hands, there are three handshakes. If four people shake hands with one another, we can picture the number of handshakes by drawing four dots (for people) and connecting the dots with segments (for handshakes). Then we count the segments (six). Use this method to count the number of handshakes that will take place between Bill, Phil, Jill, Lil, and Wil. New Concept Increasing Knowledge If we extend a side of a polygon, we form an exterior angle. In this figure ∠1 is an exterior angle, and ∠2 is an interior angle. Notice that these angles are supplementary. That is, the sum of their measures is 180º. Recall from Lesson 90 that a full turn measures 360º. So if Elizabeth makes three turns to get around a park, she has turned a total of 360º. Likewise, if she makes four turns to get around a park, she has also turned 360º. The sum of the measures of angles 1, 2, and 3 is 360°. The sum of the measures of angles 1, 2, 3, and 4 is 360°. Thinking Skill Verify Act out the turns Elizabeth made to verify the number of degrees. L E S S O N Saxon Math Course 1"
"If Elizabeth makes three turns to get around the park, then each turn averages 120º. 360° 3 turns 120° per turn If she makes four turns to get around the park, then each turn averages 90º. 360° 4 turns 90° per turn Recall that these turns correspond to exterior angles of the polygons and that the exterior and interior angles at a turn are supplementary. Since the exterior angles of a triangle average 120º, the interior angles must average 60º. A triangle has three interior angles, so the sum of the interior angles is 180º (3 × 60º = 180º). The sum of the interior angles of a triangle is 180º. The sum of angles 1, 2, and 3 is 180°. Since the exterior angles of a quadrilateral average 90º, the interior angles must average 90º. So the sum of the four interior angles of a quadrilateral is 360º (4 × 90º = 360º). The sum of the interior angles of a quadrilateral is 360º. The sum of angles 1, 2, 3, and 4 is 360°. Example 1 What is m A in  ABC? Solution The measures of the interior angles of a triangle total 180º. m∠A + 60º + 70º = 180º Since the measures of ∠B and ∠C total 130º, m∠A is 50º. C A B 60° 70°"
"Saxon Math Course 1 Example 2 What is mT in quadrilateral QRST? Solution The measures of the interior angles of a quadrilateral total 360º. m∠T + 80º + 80º + 110º = 360º The measures of ∠Q, ∠R, and ∠S total 270º. So m∠T is 90º. Practice Set Quadrilateral ABCD is divided into two triangles by segment AC. Use for problems a–c. B A C D a. What is the sum of m∠1, m∠2, and m∠3? b. What is the sum of m∠4, m∠5, and m∠6? c. Generalize What is the sum of the measures of the four interior angles of the quadrilateral? d. What is m∠P in △PQR? e. What is the measure of each interior angle of a regular quadrilateral? f. Model Elizabeth made five left turns as she ran around the park. Draw a sketch that shows the turns in her run around the park. Then find the average number of degrees in each turn. Written Practice Strengthening Concepts 1. (12, 72) When the sum of 1 2 and 1 4 is divided by the product of 1 2 and 1 4, what is the quotient? * 2. (95) Analyze Jenny is 5 1 2 feet tall. She is how many inches tall? 3. (77) If 4 5 of the 200 runners finished the race, how many runners did not finish the race? R Q S T 80° 110° 80° P R Q 75° 30° R Q S T 80° 110° 80°"
